DURBAN - SOUTH AFRICA'S Covid-19 cases have increased to 1 575 471 with more than 1000 new infections reported on Sunday. Health Minister, Dr Zweli Mkhize, confirmed that SA had recorded 1101 new cases reported in the last 24 hours. A total of 23 more Covid-19-related deaths have been reported, which brings the total to 54 148 deaths. Eastern Cape - 7 Free State - 4 Gauteng - 7 KwaZulu-Natal - 4 Western Cape - 1 "The number of tests conducted to date is 10 530 979. Of these 22 469  tests were completed since the last report. Our cumulative recoveries today stand at 1 501 185, representing a recovery rate of 95%," Mkhize said.   IOL